  This document describes the usage of runharness, the Trilinos Framework test
  harness manager.
  
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
I.  Prerequisites

  In order for the test harness to work, you must have the following in place:
  
    1.  A well-formed runharness config file.
    2.  The appropriate files refered to by your config file.
       
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
II.  Execution

  To execute the Trilinos Framework test harness, simply type:
  
    cd /PATH/TO/Trilinos/commonTools/test/harness/
    perl unharness --help
            
  Refer to this help output for the most up-to-date information on usage and
  available options.  (You can use "./" instead of "perl " if your system's
  perl interpreter resides at /usr/bin/perl)

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------